description:
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fast forward your career by joining our digital workplace programme team. A Trust wide programme supporting all our colleagues by delivering modern digital workplace solutions based on the NHS Digital national Microsoft O365 service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for the project management and implementation of a portfolio of digital workplace programme projects in adherence to Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust (ICHT) ICT Strategy, including the management of NHS.net mail refresh dependencies, adoption of the NHS Joiners Movers Leavers service, assessment and regular local administrator communications on the NHS mail management portal refresh, design and implementation of the NHSD O365 service, and supporting other ICT teams with o365 desktop distribution and EM&amp;S services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Using project management methodology and other relevant standards as appropriate, you will manage the portfolio of projects within time, budget and scope tolerances, ensuring congruence and alignment with other projects and service development initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will at all times ensure consistency with the aims and requirements of internal and external bodies, for example senior clinicians, end users, user groups, NHS bodies and third party suppliers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a flexible approach to working hours to meet the needs of the individual and the service. Please talk to us at interview about the flexibility you may need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brian Mitchell email brian.mitchell5@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
